\f0\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 sbrk returns (void*)-1 and sets errno to ENOMEM. The reason is that you can't shrink the break below where it started \'97 that would eat into the BSS/data segments of your own program, which the OS refuses. It's a safety guard: you can grow the heap freely, but you can't collapse it into your program's own static memory.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

